RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPECTRIER moved three wide to the front near the far turn, shook off challenge then increased advantage while kept to his task. RUTHENIAN bid wide with the winner into the final turn, continued well but was second best. FATHER GLADO set a pressured pace in the two path, lost the lead then was in tight near the three eighths pole, rebid wide but was no threat. EL PATOJO trailed far behind then caught a fading opponent late. SIDNEY'S BID was urged to keep up inside, steadied and bobbled slightly nearing the three eighths pole and faded. A claim of foul by the rider of SIDNEY'S BID against the winner for interference near the three eighths pole was dismissed.
